Personally I have traveled and lived in Germany for 4 years and visited several other countries. I was born and raised in the good old USA and am glad to be back because after all it is home. Everything here is so damn convenient and I took it for granted because it was all I knew. After seeing what other countries have to offer it is still my opinion that USA is still #1. Yea Germany has nice infrastructure such as the autobahn but their culture is so weird compared to what I am used to. Also take into consideration that most of what you think you know about the U.S. has been filtered through the media. Nobody likes to hear about good news or boring stories so what gets played the most are the bad things that do happen here. I will admit, we are not perfect but if I want feel like going to the store and getting groceries at 11pm on a Sunday Walmart is there for me. Try doing that in Germany because everything is closed on Sunday. I will raise my children here because they have the freedom to choose what they want to be when they grow up.
